6 (c) No person appointed pursuant to subsection (a) shall take office
7 unless such appointment is certified by the secretary of state to the
8 United States senate. The secretary shall not certify any person as being
9 appointed to fill a vacancy in the office of United States senator unless
10 such person is appointed in accordance with this section.
11 New Sec. 2. (a) Except as otherwise provided, within 10 calendar
12 days of a vacancy occurring in the office of United States senator, the
13 office of state treasurer or the office of the commissioner of insurance, the
14 joint committee on vacancy appointments shall be established by
15 appointment of the members of the joint committee. Each of this state's
16 congressional districts shall be represented by at least two members of the
17 joint committee who shall be residents thereof. The joint committee shall
18 consist of 12 members as follows:
19 (1) The president of the senate, or a member of the senate designated
20 by the president;
21 (2) one member of the senate appointed by the president;
22 (3) the speaker of the house of representatives, or a member of the
23 house of representatives designated by the speaker;
24 (4) one member of the house of representatives appointed by the
25 speaker;
26 (5) two members of the senate appointed by the majority leader of the
27 senate;
28 (6) two members of the house of representatives appointed by the
29 majority leader of the house of representatives;
30 (7) one member of the senate appointed by the vice president of the
31 senate;
32 (8) one member of the house of representatives appointed by the
33 speaker pro tem of the house of representatives;
34 (9) one member of the senate appointed by the minority leader of the
35 senate; and
36 (10) one member of the house of representatives appointed by the
37 minority leader of the house of representatives.
38 (b) Of the members named or appointed under subsections (a)(1),
39 (a)(2), (a)(5) and (a)(7), each of this state's congressional districts shall
40 be represented by at least one such member who shall be a resident
41 thereof. Of the members named or appointed under subsections (a)(3),
42 (a)(4), (a)(6) and (a)(8), each of this state's congressional districts shall
43 be represented by at least one such member who shall be a resident

