8 the chairperson of the joint committee and the speaker of the house of
9 representatives, or the speaker's designee, shall be the vice chairperson.
10 The vice chairperson shall exercise all the powers of the chairperson in the
11 absence of the chairperson.
12 (d)(e) The joint committee on vacancy appointments shall meet at any
13 time and at any place within the state on call of the chairperson. Members
14 of the joint committee shall receive compensation and travel expenses and
15 subsistence expenses or allowances as provided in K.S.A. 75-3212, and
16 amendments thereto, when attending meetings of such committee.
17 (e)(f) The first meeting of the joint committee shall be held within 30
18 calendar days of a vacancy occurring in the office of United States
19 senator, the office of state treasurer or the office of the commissioner of
20 insurance.
21 New Sec. 3. (a) The joint committee on vacancy appointments shall
22 review candidates to fill the vacancy described in section 2, and
23 amendments thereto. Such review shall include verifying that such
24 candidate satisfies federal and state requirements to hold such office and to
25 be appointed to fill a vacancy in such office. The joint committee shall
26 conduct one or more public hearings and shall grant each candidate an
27 opportunity to be heard before the joint committee.
28 (b) Except as provided in subsection (c), at the conclusion of its
29 public hearings{ within 30 calendar days after the first meeting of the
30 joint committee}, the joint committee shall introduce a concurrent
31 resolution in each house recommending three persons as candidates to fill
32 the vacancy. No member of the joint committee shall be recommended as
33 a candidate to fill the vacancy.
34 (c) If the joint committee concludes its public hearings while the
35 legislature is not in regular or special session, then{, within 30 calendar
36 days after the first meeting of the joint committee,} the joint committee
37 shall submit a report to the governor recommending three persons as
38 candidates to fill the vacancy.
39 New Sec. 4. (a) Each house shall consider any concurrent resolution
40 that is introduced pursuant to section 3, and amendments thereto, within 10
41 days and shall either adopt such resolution or direct the joint committee to
42 reconvene to reconsider candidates to fill the vacancy.
43 (b) When directed to do so by the legislature, the joint committee

